Wim Pretorius, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pietermaritzburg &ndash; A man died after he was shot multiple times in Pietermaritzburg, KwaZulu-Natal, on Tuesday evening.Circumstances that led to the shooting are still unknown and are being investigated by the South African Police Service.According to ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth, the man, believed to be in his 30's, was found by paramedics in critical condition."His vital signs deteriorated and paramedics initiated CPR. Despite all efforts to save him, the man sadly died."He was declared dead at the scene.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.